Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery grooved vessel, the fabric is partially bright-red in section, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and faint traces of at least one line of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393871) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393871)
